---
import UntranslatedLayout from '~/layouts/UntranslatedLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '~/site.config';
import { languages } from '~/i18n/ui';

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  return Object.keys(languages).map((lang) => ({ params: { lang } }));
}

const { lang } = Astro.params;
---

<UntranslatedLayout title="Terms of Service - familiar.systems" description="Terms of service for familiar.systems.">
    <div class="pt-32 pb-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-8">Terms of Service</h1>
            <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none text-foreground/80">
                <p class="text-lg mb-6">Last updated: February 25, 2026</p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">1. Who We Are</h2>
                <p>
                    familiar.systems is operated by {siteConfig.legal?.entityName} (Org. nr. {siteConfig.legal?.orgNumber}),
                    a sole proprietorship registered in Norway. When these terms say "we", "us", or "familiar.systems",
                    they mean {siteConfig.legal?.entityName}.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">2. What familiar.systems Is</h2>
                <p>
                    familiar.systems is an AI-assisted campaign wiki for tabletop RPG game masters.
                    It helps you capture session content and build a knowledge base of your campaign world.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">3. Your Content</h2>
                <p>
                    Everything you create in familiar.systems belongs to you: campaigns, notes, characters, maps, and session recordings.
                    We do not claim ownership of your content. We use it only to provide and improve the service.
                </p>
                <p>
                    You are responsible for the content you create. Do not use familiar.systems to store or distribute
                    illegal material.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">4. AI Features</h2>
                <p>
                    familiar.systems uses AI to process your session audio, extract entities, and suggest edits to your campaign.
                    All AI-generated suggestions require your explicit approval before they modify your campaign data.
                    AI output may be inaccurate. You are responsible for reviewing and accepting suggestions.
                </p>
                <p>
                    By default, audio you upload may be used to improve speech recognition models within familiar.systems.
                    This is limited to speech recognition: the models that convert sound into text. These models are used
                    exclusively within familiar.systems and are never sold or licensed to third parties. Your audio and campaign
                    content are never used to train generative AI models (such as large language models), and will never
                    appear in another user's experience. You can opt out of speech recognition training at any time in your
                    account settings. See our <a href={`/${lang}/privacy`} class="text-primary hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">5. Account & Authentication</h2>
                <p>
                    You need an account to use familiar.systems. Authentication is handled by a third-party provider (Hanko).
                    If you choose to sign in via Google or Apple, some account data may be processed outside the EU/EEA
                    by those providers. See our <a href={`/${lang}/privacy`} class="text-primary hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">6. Acceptable Use</h2>
                <p>
                    Do not abuse the service. This includes, but is not limited to: attempting to access other users' data,
                    using the service for automated data extraction, or deliberately overloading the infrastructure.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">7. Availability & Liability</h2>
                <p>
                    We aim to keep familiar.systems available and reliable, but we cannot guarantee uninterrupted service.
                    We are not liable for data loss, downtime, or indirect damages arising from your use of the service.
                    Our total liability is limited to the amount you have paid us in the 12 months preceding the claim.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">8. Termination</h2>
                <p>
                    You can delete your account at any time. We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these terms.
                    On termination, we will make your data available for export for a reasonable period before deletion.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">9. Changes to These Terms</h2>
                <p>
                    We may update these terms from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via email
                    or an in-app notice at least 30 days before they take effect. Continued use of the service
                    after the effective date constitutes acceptance.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">10. Governing Law</h2>
                <p>
                    These terms are governed by Norwegian law. Disputes are subject to the jurisdiction of the
                    Norwegian courts, with Oslo as the legal venue.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4 text-foreground">11. Contact</h2>
                <p>
                    Questions about these terms? Reach us at
                    <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.contact?.email?.support}`} class="text-primary hover:underline">{siteConfig.contact?.email?.support}</a>.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</UntranslatedLayout>
